<A NAME=135Eastwood b.s.-GUTS>
<H3><IMG SRC=script.gif ALIGN=left HSPACE=5>Eastwood b.s.-GUTS</H3><BR>
THE ARTICHOKE FIELDS SURROUNDING HIGHWAY ONE JUST SOUTH OF CARMEL HAVE BEEN AROUND FOR YEARS. IT AND THE BORDERING LAND WILD AND UNTOUCHED BY DEVELOPERS.
<P>
TODAY, IT WAS PRETTY MUCH GUARANTEED THAT IT WILL STAY THAT WAY. THANKS TO A SIX-MILLION DOLLAR DONATION BY CLINT AND MAGGIE EASTWOOD.
<P>
THE ACTOR AND HIS EX-WIFE, WHO REMAIN BUSINESS PARTNERS. TODAY DONATED MORE THAN 130 ACRES OF THEIR PROPERTY EAST OF HIGHWAY ONE, TO BE SPLIT WITH THE BIG SUR LAND TRUST, MONTEREY COUNTY, AND CAL AM.
<P>
THOUGH HE ATTENDED TODAY'S ANNOUNCEMENT PARTY IN CARMEL, CLINT EASTWOOD TRIED TO KEEP A LOW PROFILE. PREFERRING TO GIVE OTHERS THE LIMELIGHT.
<P>
PREVIOUSLY DESTINED TO BECOME A SUBDIVISION OF 82 HOMES, MUCH OF THE LAND WILL NOW PERMANENTLY REMAIN OPEN SPACE. 
<P>
THE MONTEREY COUNTY AND CAL AM PORTION WILL BE USED TO STUDY FLOOD CONTROL AND WATER USAGE ALONG THE CARMEL RIVER. AND THE REST WILL BE KEPT FOR AGRICULTURE.
<P>
=====BUTT =====
<P>

